def barplot_(df, data_col, size=(25, 10), 
             fontsize_=16, labelsize_=14, 
             alp=0.5, count_plot=2, title_="", 
             save=False, save_path=".", form='png'):
    """
    df: DataFrame
    data_col: ((), ()..) tuples(tuple()) column names
    size: graph size
    alp: alpha param
    fontsize_: fontsize
    labelsize_: labelsize
    title_: title
    count_plot: how much barplots
    save: save to PDF
    """

    if count_plot > 1:    
        figure, ax = plt.subplots(1, count_plot, sharey=True, figsize=size)
        for i, data in enumerate(data_col):
            sns.barplot(y=data[0], x=data[1], data=df, alpha=alp, ax=ax[i])
            ax[i].set_title(f'{data[1]}', fontsize=fontsize_)
    else:
        figure = plt.figure(figsize=size)
        plt.title(title_, fontsize=fontsize_)
        plt.tick_params(labelsize=labelsize_)
        sns.barplot(y=df[data_col[0]], x=df[data_col[1]], alpha=alp)
        plt.show()
        
    if save:
        figure.savefig(f'{title_}.{form}')
In [11]:
def stack_bar(df, size=(20,15), title_="borrower_genders", 
              fontsize_=16, ylabel_=None, 
              xlabel_=None, stacked_=True, 
              title_size=18,
              bbox_to_anchor_=(1.2, 1),
              save=True,
              save_path=".", form='png'):
    figure = plt.figure(figsize=size)
    plot = df.plot.barh(
        figsize=size
        , fontsize=fontsize_
        , stacked=stacked_
        , title=title_)
    plot.title.set_size(title_size)
    plot.legend(loc=1, bbox_to_anchor=bbox_to_anchor_, fontsize=fontsize_)
    plot.set(ylabel=ylabel_, xlabel=xlabel_)
    plt.show()
    
    if save:
        plot.get_figure().savefig(f'{title_}.{form}')

def multi_bar(df, size=(20, 100), title_="sector activity", count=15, 
              fontsize_=18, rotation_=90, save=True, save_path=".", form='pdf'):
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(count, 1, figsize = size)
    for i in range(len(df_kiva_loans_bar.columns)):
        data_bar = df.iloc[:, i].dropna()
        ax[i].set_title(data_bar.name, fontsize=fontsize_)
        ax[i].set_xticklabels(data_bar.index, rotation=rotation_)
        ax[i].bar(data_bar.index, data_bar.values)
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=1)
    
    if save:
        fig.savefig(f'{title_}.{form}')

def world_map(df, size=(40, 40), mark='o', linestyle_='', columns=None, 
             save=True, save_path=".", title_="wait_time", form='png'):
    
    if columns is None:
        columns = ['country', 'wait_time', 'point']
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=size)
    ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1, projection=ccrs.PlateCarree())
    for data in df[columns].values:
        ax.plot(data[2][1], data[2][0], 
                marker=mark, 
                linestyle=linestyle_, 
                markersize=data[1], 
                label=data[0])
        if data[1] > 15:
            ax.text(x=data[2][1], y=data[2][0],
                     s=data[0],
                     color="red", fontsize=10)


    ax.stock_img()
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.BORDERS)
    ax.coastlines(resolution='110m')
    
    if save:
        fig.savefig(f'{title_}.{form}')

def distributions(df, value, size=(20, 10), save=True, save_path=".", title_="wait_time", form='png'):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=size)
    sns.distplot(df[value])
    plt.show()
    
    if save:
        fig.savefig(f'{title_}.{form}')
